President Joe Biden delivered a speech at the Pennsylvania Convention Center in Philadelphia, where he expressed his gratitude to organized labor and union workers. He emphasized his commitment to unions and his pride in being the most pro-union president in American history. Biden highlighted the achievements of his administration, such as the passing of the American Rescue Plan, the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, and the Inflation Reduction Act. He also discussed his plans to create jobs, invest in American manufacturing, and ensure that the wealthy and big corporations pay their fair share of taxes. Biden called for unity and urged the audience to join him in the fight to protect the progress made and secure a better future for the country.